HEADWORD: Quadriceps
<hw>Quad"ri*ceps</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>qyattuor</ets> four + <ets>caput</ets> head.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The great extensor muscle of the knee, divided
above into four parts which unite in a single tendon at the
knee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

